Frequently Asked Questions

What is speech therapy?

Speech therapy is a specialized service that helps individuals improve their speech, language, communication, and swallowing skills. It focuses on diagnosing and treating speech delays, language disorders, stuttering, articulation problems, and other communication challenges.

Who needs speech therapy?

Speech therapy is beneficial for:

Children with delayed speech or unclear pronunciation

Individuals with stuttering or voice issues

People recovering from stroke, brain injury, or neurological conditions

Those with developmental disorders such as Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD)

Anyone facing difficulty in understanding or expressing language effectively

How do I know if my child needs speech therapy?

If your child is struggling to communicate, not meeting speech milestones, or you notice unclear speech, limited vocabulary, or frustration during communication, its best to schedule an evaluation with a qualified speech-language pathologist.

Do you provide online/teletherapy sessions as well?

Yes we offer teletherapy using secure video platforms for eligible clients.

What age groups do you treat?

We provide therapy for children, adolescents, and adults. Each therapy plan is customized according to age, diagnosis, and individual needs.

How do I book an appointment?

Use the booking form in our website or call/whatsapp 0312 4500050.

Do you work with cochlear implant users ?

Yes we provide post-implant rehabilitation and hearing-aid follow-up services.
